people have spoken, and the awards have been given!&nbsp; Here are the results:</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2020-top-providers-copy.png.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-full wp-image-26426 alignnone litespeed-loaded\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2020-top-providers-copy.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"625\" height=\"600\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2020-top-providers-copy.png.webp 625w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2020-top-providers-copy-300x288.png.webp 300w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2020-top-providers-copy.png.webp 625w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2020-top-providers-copy-300x288.png.webp 300w\" data-was-processed=\"true\"></p><p>Congrats to <a href=\"https://racknerd.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">RackNerd</a>, <a href=\"https://nexusbytes.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">NexusBytes</a>, and <a href=\"https://hosthatch.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">HostHatch</a>!</p><p>Voting was close near the top, so it\u2019s worth mentioning the rest of the top 10:</p><p>4. <a href=\"https://virmach.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">VirMach</a></p><p>5. <a href=\"https://buyvm.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">BuyVM</a></p><p>6. <a href=\"https://www.hetzner.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Hetzner</a></p><p>7. <a href=\"https://mxroute.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">MXroute</a> and <a href=\"https://www.ovh.com/world/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">OVH</a> (tie)</p><p>9. <a href=\"https://hostsolutions.ro/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">HostSolutions</a></p><p>10. <a href=\"https://hosting.gullo.me/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Gullo\u2019s Hosting</a></p><p>See the <a href=\"https://www.lowendtalk.com/discussion/169775/let-provider-poll-2020-results/p1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">results thread</a> for full details.</p><h3>How Does a Provider Become a Best Provider?</h3><p>From what I\u2019ve seen, LEB/LET readers value:</p><p><strong>Price:</strong> Go figure with a name like LowEndTalk/LowEndBox!&nbsp; LEB/LET readers are always looking for great value for the price.&nbsp; Paradoxically, though, the community usually reacts poorly to obviously unsustainable offers.&nbsp; So it\u2019s not the craziest offer that always wins the community\u2019s support but it\u2019s a key factor in the overall decision.</p><p><strong>Reliability:&nbsp;</strong>High uptime, few problems, lack of network hiccups, and solid performance all go into this category.&nbsp; No one is expecting five nines but flakey hardware, iffy networks, and slothful servers mean migrating users.</p><p><strong>Transparency and Community Engagement:</strong> A lot of problems can be overcome by communicating frequently and often with the community you serve.</p><p>Again, congratulations to the winners and we hope to see all of them (and others!) back on the 2021 board.</p><div class=\"relpost-thumb-wrapper\"><div class=\"relpost-thumb-container\"><h3>Related posts:</h3><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div class=\"relpost-block-container\"><a class=\"relpost-block-single\" href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/community-news-kvm-ryzen-nvme-ssd-vps-by-racknerd-now-available-in-new-york/\"><div style=\"width: 150px; height: 215px;\"><div class=\"relpost-block-single-image\" alt=\"Community News: KVM Ryzen NVMe SSD VPS by RackNerd Now Available in New York\" style=\"background: transparent url(https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/amd-ryzen-dedicated-servers-150x150.jpg) no-repeat scroll 0% 0%; width: 150px; height: 150px;\"></div><div class=\"relpost-block-single-text\" style=\"font-family: Arial;  font-size: 12px;  color: #333333;\">Community News: KVM Ry